<div style="font-size:25px"><center>Overview</center></div>
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}

{{Blurimage|file=RestingPlaceImage.webp|align=right|width=350px|caption=A '''Resting Place''' in [[Level 0]]. Photographer succumbed to '''Resting Hyperinsomnia''' in 8 days.}}'''Resting Places''' are rare phenomena appearing within most enclosed non-Euclidean levels. They have been observed in 218 levels to date, with only one '''Resting Place''' appearing per level. Only one wanderer can be in the same instance of a '''Resting Place''', with wanderers being sent to their own copy of the area on entry.

The entrance of a '''Resting Place''' appears as a plain wooden door on the wall of any enclosed non-Euclidean level. This door is commonly decorated with stickers to resemble the level, for example, the '''Resting Place''' within Level 0's door is decorated with stickers matching the level's wallpaper. Touching the door while outside of the '''Resting Place''' will [[No-Clipping|noclip]] the wanderer into the '''Resting Place'''. Touching the door while inside of the '''Resting Place''' will noclip the wanderer into a random location within the level the '''Resting Place''' is within.

In all accounts of '''Resting Places''', they appear as rooms matching the level's appearance, with a single plastic chair in the middle of the room. Sound in the room is muffled, and any noise made will comfort the wanderer inside. Within a '''Resting Place''', all physical ailments afflicting a wanderer are cured. In addition, mental hazards lose their effect on any wanderer within a '''Resting Place'''.

'''Resting Places''' will only appear if a wanderer is near death, or has a high risk of death within the next hour (for instance, if one is being chased by a large number of entities, or is exhausted). Upon the appearance of the door leading to the '''Resting Place''', the wanderer will find themselves irrevocably drawn toward the '''Resting Place'''.

Wanderers may spend up to 24 hours within the '''Resting Place''', after which they will be ejected out of the '''Resting Place''' and sent to a random location within the level as if they had touched the door.





''Appearances are not as they seem, however. These innocent locations are not peaceful. If you see the door... well, let's just say it would be better to die another way.''





<div style="font-size:25px"><center>Resting Hyperinsomnia</center></div>
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}

'''Resting Hyperinsomnia''' is the end result of any wanderer's entry into a '''Resting Place'''. It is a disease with three phases, similar to [[Phenomenon 35|Roth Syndrome]] and other Backrooms illnesses. '''Resting Hyperinsomnia''' is invariably fatal.

<div style="font-size:20px"><center>Resting Hyperinsomnia: Phase 1</center></div>
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}

The first phase of '''Resting Hyperinsomnia''' begins 2 to 4 hours after leaving a '''Resting Place'''. During this phase, the wanderer is incredibly tired, yet cannot sleep for longer than four hours. This has an extreme negative effect on wanderers' mental health and sanity.

<div style="font-size:20px"><center>Resting Hyperinsomnia: Phase 2</center></div>
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}

The second phase of '''Resting Hyperinsomnia''' begins 24 to 30 hours after leaving a '''Resting Place'''. Effects on wanderers afflicted by Phase 2 '''Resting Hyperinsomnia''' include extreme rage, a tendency toward violence, and partial to complete insanity.

<div style="font-size:20px"><center>Resting Hyperinsomnia: Phase 3</center></div>
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}

The third phase of '''Resting Hyperinsomnia''' begins seven days after leaving a '''Resting Place'''. Initial effects of this phase include incredible anger and rage. As the phase continues, afflicted wanderers become increasingly despondent, eventually losing all sanity and transitioning into [[Phenomenon 35|Roth Syndrome]].
